  "system": {
    "description": "<p>The difference between a diplomat and a spy is the quality of the intelligence they bring to their superiors. Ceasefires, alliances, and treaties don't last long in The War, and the clever ones will make the most of that reprieve by preparing for when it fails. The best use of that time is to employ an Envoy. Skillfully negotiating the celebrations, deals, and deceptions of politics to pull the most out of such opportunities, they bring intel home with a smile and handshake.</p>",
